HEADWORD: Madecassee
<hw>Mad`e*cas"see</hw>
<pr>(?)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>prop. n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A native or
inhabitant of Madagascar, or Madecassee. See <er>Malagasy</er></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The language of the natives of Madagascar.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Madecassee</ent>⟦br⟧

